      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OBSIDIAN DREAM (3) looks well placed here following a 2.3L defeat over 1200m at Gosford. Both maidens she's been part of are stronger than this and getting onto a more spacious track may suit. Looks to get every chance from the draw for JVO and she can get the job done this time. MR MAGNIFICENCE (2) hit the line nicely in a recent trial and showed enough class in his debut campaign to think he won't be a maiden for much longer. He should be prominent from the outset for Owen and if he can return somewhere near his best, he'll be right in the finish. THINK I'M IN (1) is on debut for the Pfieffer barn after hitting the line nicely in a recent trial. Guymer's booking is a good push for his chances. He'll need some luck from the inside draw, but he can make his presence felt if the gaps come. CAPITAL BABE (6) is knocking on the door of a maiden victory and won't be far away. WAVE DANCER (5) won't be far away yet again.",
